1. Objective
To validate the Login functionality of the application using automated test scripts and ensure correct behavior for valid and invalid inputs.
2. Scope
In Scope:
- Login page UI validation
- Valid login scenario
- Invalid login scenario
- Error message validation
- symbol and alphabet validation 

 Out of Scope:
- Database testing
- Performance testing
- Security testing

3. Test Strategy
- Manual test cases designed first
- Automation using Selenium & PyTest
- Page Object Model implementation
- Data-driven testing using JSON

 4. Test Environment
- OS: Windows
- Browser: Chrome
- Language: Python 3.x

 5. Entry Criteria
- Application is accessible
- Test data available

 6. Exit Criteria
- All planned test cases executed
- Test results documented

#7. Risks & Mitigation
- Browser compatibility issues â†’ handled using WebDriver Manager
